description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;PREVIOUS APPLICANTS NEED NOT APPLY&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Home Assessment Reablement Team (HART) is looking for Reablement Support Workers to join our community based service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Home Assessment Reablement Team has the four following teams, Oxford City (based from Unipart Business House), North Oxfordshire (based from the Horton General Hospital), West Oxfordshire (also based from the Horton General Hospital) and South Oxfordshire (based from Abingdon Health and Wellbeing Centre). &lt;strong&gt;We are currently recruiting to our Oxford City and South Oxfordshire teams. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking to recruit Reablement Support Workers to work as part of a large team providing care and reablement support to service users in their own homes. We can offer weekly contracted hours of anything up to 36hrs, worked over a 2 week rota to include every other weekend. Care is delivered to service users between the hours of 7am and 10pm.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;If this is the job for you please apply online now.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;You will earn an annual spot salary of £21,210 (pro rata for part time hours).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will need to &lt;strong&gt;hold a full driving licence&lt;/strong&gt; and have a reliable car available for work. Mileage payments will be paid at 45p per business mile.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are shortlisted for this post, you will be required to complete a pre-interview assessment and will only be invited to interview, if you score over 70%.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interviews will be held via Microsoft Teams.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Closing date 16 November 2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Kimberley Green, 01865 234956 or email Kimberley.Green@ouh.nhs.uk&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
